window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>Prepare yourself for the shocking, the strange, and the terrifying in Ambrose Bierce’s 1893 story collection <i>Can Such Things Be?</i> One of the greatest masters of horror brings you 25 tales of the supernatural and the unexplained. Whether in stories of ghosts sending desperate warnings to their human counterparts, psychics attempting to bridge unknown dimensions, howling werewolves, or a robot who takes on a life of his own, Bierce plumbs the depths of fear and fascination. Spooky thrills and mind-bending mysteries await all who dare to open the cover of <i>Can Such Things Be?</i></p>"; 
